                            <div class="spacer-double" style="background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat;"></div>
                            <div class="col-6" style="background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat;">
                                <div class="de_count wow fadeInUp animated" style="background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; visibility: visible; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                                    <h3><span class="timer" data-to="7" data-speed="3000">7</span>%</h3>
                                    <h4>Proportion of<br> Chinese population <br>in <strong class="">1861</strong></h4>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="spacer-10" style="background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat;"></div>
                            <img class="img-resize" src="@Url.Content("~/Content/Customer/images/study-case-single/main/cn/1861.png")" class="img-fluid rounded-10 wow zoomIn animated" alt="" style="visibility: visible; animation-name: zoomIn;">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6" style="background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat;">
                    <h1><strong class="text-danger">Chinese</strong> Community in Victoria </h1>
                    <p>Chinese settlers first arrived in Victoria during the gold rush era, facing hardships and contributing significantly to the region's development. By 1861, their vibrant community formed 7% of the population, with Little Bourke Street in Melbourne becoming a cultural and business hub. Despite facing immigration restrictions, the Chinese community thrived, diversifying into various sectors. The 1970s saw the removal of discriminatory policies, leading to strengthened ties and a significant increase in the China-born population in Victoria, highlighting their enduring legacy and contribution to Victorian society.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
