                                    <h3 class="de-timeline-title">Economic Diversification and Community Contributions</h3>
                                    <p>As gold resources dwindled, many Chinese settlers turned to market gardening, small businesses, and various trades, such as laundry operations and medicine, contributing significantly to local economies.</p>
